COLLISION DAMAGE WAIVER- COLLISION DAMAGE WAIVER -CDW- IS OPTIONAL AND REDUCES THE AMOUNT OF THE RENTERS DAMAGE RESPONSIBILITY TO THE SUM OF THE EXCESS. IF CDW IS DECLINED THEN THE RENTER MAY BE LIABLE FOR THE WHOLE VALUE OF THE DAMAGE OR LOSS. THE COST OF CDW PER DAY VARIES FROM EACH CAR CLASS. CDW RATES RANGE FROM UP TO 30.00 EUR PLUS VAT PER DAY WITH THE DEDUCTIBLE UP TO THE AMOUNT OF 962 EUR. EXCESS WITHOUT CDW EQUALS FULL VALUE OF THE RENTAL VEHICLE. SUPER COLLISION DAMAGE WAIVER- SUPER COLLISION DAMAGE WAIVER -SCDW- IS OPTIONAL AND CAN ONLY BE PURCHASED IN CONJUNCTION WITH CDW AND CANNOT BE PURCHASED ALONE. SCDW COVERS THE EXCESS ON CDW TO ZERO IN CASE OF THEFT OF THE VEHICLE OR AFTER COLLISION. NOT APPLICABLE WHEN DUE TO THE DRIVERS NEGLIGENCE. THE COST OF SUPER CDW PER DAY VARIES FROM EACH CAR CLASS. SUPER CDW RATES RANGE FROM UP TO 22.72 EUR PLUS VAT PER DAY WITH THE DEDUCTIBLE UP TO THE AMOUNT OF 962 EUR. CDW-TP COLLISION DAMAGE WAIVER REDUCES THE AMOUNT OF THE RENTERS DAMAGE RESPONSIBILITY TO THE SUM OF THE DEDUCTIBLE. IF CDW IS DECLINED, THEN THE RENTER MAY BE LIABLE FOR THE WHOLE VALUE OF THE DAMAGE OR LOSS. CDW IS OPTIONAL IF NOT INCLUDED IN THE RATES.
CREDIT CARDS ACCEPTABLE FOR DEPOSIT AX CA VI CREDIT CARDS ACCEPTABLE FOR GUARANTEE AX CA VI

ONE WAY RENTALS- DOMESTIC ONE WAYS ARE AVAILABLE FOR ALL LOCATIONS WITHIN CONTINENTAL SPAIN FOR CONSUMER AND TOUR BOOKINGS. COST IS AVAILABLE UPON BOOKING FOR ALL CARS. THERE IS NO MINIMUM LENGTH OF RENTAL. DOMESTIC ONE WAY RENTALS WITHIN THE SAME CITY ARE FREE OF CHARGE. DOMESTIC ONE WAY RENTALS ARE NOT ALLOWED BETWEEN ISLAND AND MAINLAND OR VICE VERSA OR AMONG ISLANDS. DOMESTIC ONE WAY RENTALS ARE ALLOWED BETWEEN LOCATIONS ON THE SAME ISLAND IN THE CANARY ISLANDS. INTERNATIONAL ONE WAY RENTALS ARE NOT ALLOWED. CROSS BORDER POLICY- CARS CAN BE DRIVEN INTO THE FOLLOWING COUNTRIES- ANDORRA-AUSTRIA-BELGIUM-FRANCE-GERMANY-GIBRALTAR- LUXEMBOURG-ITALY-MONACO-NETHERLANDS-PORTUGAL- SWITZERLAND. OUTSIDE SPAIN INSURANCE IS REQUIRED FOR ANY CROSS BORDER RENTAL EXCEPT PORTUGAL AND ANDORRA. RENTALS OF 1-10 DAYS -EUR 40.00 PLUS VAT RENTALS OF 11-27 DAYS -EUR 65.00 PLUS VAT RENTALS OF 28-99 DAYS -EUR 95.00 PLUS VAT CARS CANNOT BE DRIVEN INTO ANY OTHER COUNTRIES. CUSTOMER MUST ADVISE THE CAR WILL BE DRIVEN OUT OF SPAIN AT THE BEGINNING OF THE RENTAL. CROSS BORDER INTO GERMANY- PLEASE BE ADVISED THAT THE FOLLOWING AREAS IN GERMANY WILL REQUIRE AN EMISSIONS STICKER STATING THE EMISSION OF THE VEHICLE INTENDED TO ENTER THE FOLLOWING AREAS- BERLIN-COLOGNE-HANNOVER WITHOUT THIS STICKER THE DRIVER OF THE VEHICLE WILL BE FINED UP TO 40.00 EUR EVEN IF THE CAR IS REGISTERED ABROAD. SHOULD THE CAR NOT HAVE THE EMISSIONS STICKER THEN THIS CAN BE PURCHASED AT MOST GARAGES.
A REFUELING CHARGE WILL BE APPLIED IF CAR IS RETURNED WITH LESS FUEL THAN AT TIME OF RENTAL.

THIRD PARTY INSURANCE- THIRD PARTY LIABILITY INSURANCE -TPL- IS MANDATORY AND COVERS THE DRIVER AND THE OWNER FOR THIRD PARTY CLAIMS AGAINST HIM/HER FOR DAMAGE CAUSED BY THE HIRE VEHICLE TPL IS INCLUDED IN THE RATE. COVER IS LIMITED TO 135 MILLION EUROS. THEFT PROTECTION- THEFT PROTECTION -TP- IS OPTIONAL AND REDUCES THE DRIVERS RESPONSIBILITY FOR LOSS OR DAMAGE TO THE CAR FOLLOWING THEFT OR ATTEMPTED THEFT AND MUST BE PURCHASED AT THE TIME OF RENTAL. TP CANNOT BE COVERED BY RENTERS CREDIT CARDS UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES. EXCESS WITHOUT TP EQUALS FULL VALUE OF THE RENTAL VEHICLE.

ADDITIONAL DRIVERS- RENTAL CONDITIONS APPLY TO ALL ADDITIONAL DRIVERS. SEE AGE REQUIREMENTS FOR RESTRICTIONS ON CAR GROUPS. ADDITIONAL DRIVERS FEE- ADDITIONAL DRIVERS FEE - 6.61 EUR PLUS VAT PER DRIVER PER DAY. MAXIMUM CHARGE - 52.89 EUR PLUS VAT. MAXIMUM ADDITIONAL DRIVERS PER RENTAL 3

PAYMENT POLICY- VISA CREDIT CARDS -ACCEPTED AMERICAN EXPRESS CARDS -ACCEPTED MASTERCARDS -ACCEPTED . CASH PAYMENTS -NOT ACCEPTED TRAVELLERS CHEQUES -NOT ACCEPTED EUROCHEQUES -NOT ACCEPTED . DEPOSITS- AN INTERNATIONAL VALID CREDIT CARD IS ALWAYS REQUIRED FOR THE DEPOSIT WHICH WILL BE HELD ON THE CREDIT CARD UNTIL THE VEHICLE IS RETURNED.
COUNTER LOCATED IN TERMINAL. CARS ARE WITHIN WALKING DISTANCE.

STATES, COUNTIES, CITIES AND OTHER GOVERNMENTAL AUTHORITIES MAY IMPOSE SALES TAXES, GROSS RECEIPTS TAXES, FEES AND OTHER MANDATORY CHARGES, SUCH AS ARENA OR STADIUM FEES, ON CUSTOMER OF CAR RENTAL COMPANIES OR CAR RENTAL TRANSACTIONS. THESE CHARGES APPEAR IN THE CHARGES SECTION OF THE RENTAL AGREEMENT. AT CERTAIN AIRPORT LOCATIONS WHERE ENTERPRISE ATESA IS AN ON AIRPORT PROVIDER, ENTERPRISE ATESA IS REQUIRED TO COLLECT OTHER MANDATORY CHARGES FROM ITS CUSTOMER AND TO REMIT THEM TO THE AIRPORT. THESE ARE SOMETIMES REFERRED TO AS CUSTOMER FACILITY CHARGES, AIRPORT FACILITY CHARGES OR TRANSPORTATION FACILITY CHARGES. THESE CHARGES ARE ALSO SET FORTH IN THE CHARGES SECTION OF THE RENTAL AGREEMENT. . THE APPROXIMATE TOTAL RENTAL COST SECTION OF THE RULE DISPLAY PROVIDES YOU WITH MORE DETAILED INFORMATION ON SPECIFIC CHARGES FOR A PARTICULAR LOCATION.

LICENSE REQUIREMENTS- RENTERS WITH NON ROMAN SCRIPT LICENSES AS WELL AS LICENSES FROM ALL COUNTRIES OUTSIDE THE EU MUST HAVE AN INTERNATIONAL LICENSE AND THEIR OWN LICENSE FROM THEIR COUNTRY OF DOMICILE. ALL DRIVERS MUST HAVE HELD A FULL LICENSE FOR A MINIMUM OF TWO YEARS. ALL DRIVERS WILL BE REQUIRED TO SHOW THEIR DRIVING LICENSE AND VALID PASSPORT AS A GENERAL RULE. AN ID CARD CAN BE USED IF IT IS WRITTEN IN ROMAN CHARACTERS AND CAN BE USED ONLY FOR COUNTRIES WITHIN THE EU. SPANISH LAW NOW STATES THAT ALL RENTAL CARS MUST HAVE A COPY OF THE RENTAL AGREEMENT WITHIN THE VALID RENTAL DATES. IF REQUESTED BY POLICE OR GUARDIA CIVIL THE RENTER MUST SHOW THE VALID RENTAL AGREEMENT. IF THIS IS OUT OF DATE THE RENTER WILL BE SUBJECT TO A FINE OF 1001.00 EUR. ANY POSSIBLE RENTAL EXTENSION MUST BE PROCESSED AT OUR RENTAL LOCATIONS BY THE CUSTOMER IN PERSON. IT CANNOT BE PROCESSED BY PHONE OR EMAIL ETC. WHILE THE VEHICLE IS REGISTERED IN ENTERPRISE ATESA RECORDS IF A RECORD OF THE RENTAL EXTENSION IS NOT CARRIED INSIDE THE CAR THE AUTHORITIES WILL ISSUE A FINE. THIS PENALTY CANNOT BE REMOVED BY SHOWING DOCUMENTS AFTER THE FINE IS APPLIED.

Additional Driver Policy

The price per additional driver will be Euro 6.61 + VAT Per day, with a maximum charge of Euro 62.80 + VAT. Maximum 3 additional drivers per rental. See Age Requirements for restrictions on car groups.

Age Requirements

Minimum rental age is 21 years for car groups EBMR, EDMR, ECMR, CCMR, CDMR, CDAR, CMMR, IWMR, IWAR, IVAR and IVMR. 25 years for PDMR and 23 years for all other car groups. A Young Driver surcharge will be applicable to drivers between 21 to 25 years of age at a charge of Euro 8.00 + VAT per day, with a maximum charge of Euro 80 + VAT per rental, and no maximum age limit (subject to the driving license expiration and license requirements).

Condition of Vehicle

Vehicle must be returned, normal wear & tear expected, in the same condition as when rented. If special cleaning is required a separate charge will be made directly to the customer

Cross Border Policy

Vehicles are permitted to be driven into Portugal, Andorra & Gibraltar (no outside Spain insurance required). Vehicles are also permitted to be driven into Austria, Germany, Belgium, France, Netherlands, Italy, Luxembourg, Monaco & Switzerland (no other countries are permitted) but "OUTSIDE SPAIN INSURANCE" must be purchased & costs are as follows: 1-10 days Euro 41.32 + VAT. 11-27 days Euro 66.12 + VAT. 28 days+ Euro 95.04 + VAT, this is purchased at the counter. Customer MUST advise the car will be driven out of Spain at the point of contract, in any case.

Please be advised that the following areas in Germany: Berlin, Cologne and Hannover will require an 'Emissions Sticker' stating the emission of the vehicle intended to enter these areas. Without this sticker, the driver of the vehicle will be fined up to EUR 40.00 even if the car is registered abroad. Should the car not have the 'Emissions Sticker', then this can be purchased at most garages.

License Requirements

Non-Roman script licenses as well as all licenses from countries out of the EU must have an International license & their license from country of domicile. All drivers must have held their full license for a minimum of two (2) years.

 

Together with their driving license, all drivers will be required to show their passport, as a general rule, or ID card, if it is written in roman characters and only for EU countries.

 

Spanish Law now states that, rental cars must have a copy of the rental agreement, within valid rental dates. If requested by police or Guardia Civil, the Lessee must show the valid rental agreement. If this is out-of date, the Lessee will be fined with 1001.00 ?.

 

So it is mandatory that any possible rental extension is processed at our rental locations by the customer, in person. It couldn?t be processed by phone, by e-mail, etc. while, even if it is registered in ATESA?s records, if it?s not carried inside the car, the authorities will issue a fine. This penalty cannot be removed by showing documents after the fine is applied.

 

One Way Rentals

Domestic one ways are available for all locations situated within Continental Spain with a EUR 35.00 + tax drop charge applicable to all tour bookings, for all cars and all lengths of rental. 

One ways between locations situated in the same city are free of charge. 

For the Canary Islands, one ways are allowed between locations situated in the same island free of charge.

One ways are not allowed between Islands and Continental Spain or among Islands.

For the Balearics, one ways are not allowed.

One ways are to be pre-booked.

Car group SVMR can not be picked up or dropped off at MADX73/MADX03 due to height parking restrictions at this station.

Out of Hours Policy

An additional charge of Euro 44.63 + VAT applies for out of hours. After hours are on request only

Payment Policy

All major Credit cards (VISA, AMEX, Master Card, Diners). Travelers Cheques and Eurocheques are not accepted. Cash rentals are not allowed. A credit card valid internationally is required and a deposit on the credit card will be held. If cards do not permit deposits, then charges will have to be made. A credit card is always required for deposits. The deposit will be the estimated rental fees plus EUR 100.00, which is held on the credit card until the car is returned. See Refueling Policy for Fuel Deposits.

Refueling Policy

For ENTERPRISE / ATESA locations: As a customer, you have a choice as to how you would like to pay for fuel. You will be provided with two options, both starting with a full tank of fuel in your vehicle at the time of rental.

Option 1: Upfront Fuel

This option allows a renter to pay for the full tank of gas at the time of rental and return the tank empty. The total Upfront Fuel charge reflected is different depending on tank size for each car model actually provided. This charge may change upon time of rental.

No refunds will be given for unused gas.

Option 2: Return Full or Pay Enterprise / Atesa for Gas

This option allows a renter to return the vehicle with a full tank of gas or pay ATESA at the end of the rental for gas used but not replaced, plus a Refuelling Fee of EUR 14,88, plus V.A.T.

 

For CICAR Locations: CICAR will often not supply the car with a full tank and expects the customer to return the vehicle with the same amount of fuel.

 

 

Roadside Assistance

In case of accident or breakdown, emergency telephone numbers are: From anywhere on the Spanish Mainland: dial 90 215 2898. From any other country: dial + 34 91 594 9363 (24 hours). A replacement car will be provided if necessary.

Special Equipment

Infant seat (CSI) Up to 18 Kg = Euro 6.61 per day plus tax, with a maximum of Euro 52.89 + tax per rental. On Request.

Child/Toddler seat (CST) up to 36 Kg = Euro 6.61 per day plus tax, with a maximum of Euro 52.89 + tax per rental. On Request.

Booster Seat (BST) over 36 Kg = Euro 6.61 per day plus tax, with a maximum of Euro 52.89 + tax per rental. On Request.

Ski Rack (SKV) = Euro 44.63 per rental plus tax.  On Request.

Snow chains (SNO) = Euro 44.63 per rental plus tax.  On Request.

Luggage rack (LUG) = Not Available.

 

GPS = Euro 7.43 per day plus tax, maximum of Euro 74.38 + tax. On Request.

GPS is only available at the following locations:

Madrid Airport, Madrid Atocha RRS, Madrid Chamartn RRS, Madrid Plaza de Espaa, Barcelona Muntaner, Barcelona Airport, Barcelona Sants RRS, Gerona Airport, Santander Airport, Bilbao Airport, Zaragoza RRS, Alicante Airport, Alicante RRS, Valencia Airport, Valencia Ave High Speed RRS, Sevilla Airport, Malaga Airport, Sevilla Santa Justa RRS, Malaga RRS, LA Corua Airport, Vigo Airport, Santiago de, Compostela Airport, Asturias Airport, Palma de Mallorca Airport, Jerez Airport, Murcia Off-Airport, Granada Off-Airport, Crdoba RRS, Almera Airport.

 

Additional charges may apply as follows:

Incase of Theft, loss, breakdown or breakage of the entire accessory or GPS unit, there is a charge of Euro 250.00 + tax (paid locally). 

In case of Theft, loss, breakdown or breakage of any other component of the GPS unit, there is a charge of Euro 30.00 + tax (paid locally). 

 

All equipments require 24 hours advance notice.

Children under 3 years must use a restraint system adapted to their weight and size. For Children up to 3 years old, whose height is less than 150cm, it is mandatory for the use of a restraint system adapted to their weight and size or, at least the use of a seatbelt.

 

We provide one fluorescent jacket per rental as the law requires, non returned jackets are charged at 8.00 Euro.

Emergency Triangles are also provided - non returned triangles sets will be charged at the market price.

Surcharges

Airport surcharge Euro 25.00 + Tax per rental.

Tax

Sales Tax 21% (Canaries only 13,5%)

Please note: sales tax is now calculated by the drop off date (rather than by pick up date).  The tax will be re-calculated at the counter if applicable as the systems can only charge this depending on the pick up date.

Collision Damage Waiver reduces the amount of the renter?s damage responsibility to the sum of the deductible.  If CDW is declined, then the renter may be liable for the whole value of the damage/loss. CDW is optional if not included in the rates.

Third Party Liability

Third Party Cover is included in all rates and covers the driver for third party claims against him/her for damage caused by the hire vehicle. TPL is included in the rate. Cover is limited to 50 million Euro.
